1
00:00:14,460 --> 00:00:18,210
[2015]

2
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:21,500
[Binjiang Province Guhua Prison]

3
00:00:29,640 --> 00:00:30,190
Boss.

4
00:00:31,710 --> 00:00:32,640
Good one.

5
00:00:34,070 --> 00:00:35,330
You've suffered a lot.

6
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:40,370
Let me light you a cigarette

7
00:00:40,430 --> 00:00:41,470
to get rid of the bad luck.

8
00:00:41,470 --> 00:00:42,400
Thank you, Boss.

9
00:00:56,110 --> 00:00:56,600
Boss,

10
00:00:56,870 --> 00:00:59,070
I need to take care of
something personal first.

11
00:00:59,070 --> 00:00:59,600
Go ahead.

12
00:01:13,789 --> 00:01:14,350
Go home.

13
00:01:16,430 --> 00:01:18,289
Your parents are waiting for you.

14
00:01:19,580 --> 00:01:22,000
[Zhou Jin's father, Zhou Songyue]
[Zhou Jin's mother, Lin Qiuyun]

15
00:01:24,150 --> 00:01:25,640
There's nothing to wait for.

16
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:26,360
Hurry back.

17
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:27,370
Jiang Cheng,

18
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,730
I'm giving you one last chance.

19
00:01:32,430 --> 00:01:33,960
Would you come back with me,

20
00:01:34,950 --> 00:01:35,810
or go with them?

21
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:37,140
Cheng,

22
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:38,310
who is she?

23
00:01:38,440 --> 00:01:39,640
Just take her with us.

24
00:01:44,070 --> 00:01:45,800
Jiang Cheng, come back with me!

25
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:47,530
Get lost!

26
00:01:48,070 --> 00:01:49,270
How pathetic are you?

27
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,580
Jiang Cheng, you bastard!

28
00:02:00,870 --> 00:02:02,120
Get up.

29
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:02,980
Get up quickly.

30
00:02:04,790 --> 00:02:05,400
Are you alright?

31
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,000
I'm fine.

32
00:02:08,210 --> 00:02:09,669
Jiang Cheng, you bastard!

33
00:03:32,270 --> 00:03:38,160
[Sunsets Secrets Regrets]

34
00:03:38,510 --> 00:03:40,920
[Episode 3]

35
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:45,360
I really don't know
if Meng Ling and Lai San

36
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:46,360
have any beef.

37
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,590
But if you're asking

38
00:03:48,590 --> 00:03:50,310
who has the biggest grudge
against Lai San around here,

39
00:03:50,310 --> 00:03:51,680
that would definitely be me.

40
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:53,560
So whether he was threatened or not,

41
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:55,220
he probably wouldn't tell me.

42
00:03:55,420 --> 00:03:57,280
What's the issue between you two?

43
00:03:58,240 --> 00:03:59,750
He disgusted me,

44
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:00,750
so I beat him up.

45
00:04:01,010 --> 00:04:02,540
Does that count as a grudge?

46
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:05,150
To be honest,

47
00:04:05,150 --> 00:04:06,910
you're really asking the wrong person.

48
00:04:06,910 --> 00:04:08,470
I just returned to Haizhou

49
00:04:08,470 --> 00:04:09,270
two weeks ago.

50
00:04:09,310 --> 00:04:11,640
I know nothing about what's going on here.

51
00:04:11,750 --> 00:04:12,470
You've taken

52
00:04:12,470 --> 00:04:13,590
who you wanted.

53
00:04:14,030 --> 00:04:15,240
My place just opened,

54
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:17,310
and a bunch of buddies are relying on me.

55
00:04:17,310 --> 00:04:18,269
If we keep holding things up,

56
00:04:18,269 --> 00:04:19,130
don't you think

57
00:04:19,510 --> 00:04:21,440
it's getting a bit inappropriate?

58
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,160
Just try to think back a little.

59
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:26,180
Where were you from July 23

60
00:04:26,630 --> 00:04:27,630
until the early hours of July 24?

61
00:04:27,630 --> 00:04:29,240
I spent the night here.

62
00:04:29,350 --> 00:04:30,880
Anyone who can verify that?

63
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:32,890
Everyone here can confirm it.

64
00:04:33,310 --> 00:04:33,950
Of course.

65
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:35,480
If you don't believe me,

66
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,000
look,

67
00:04:36,020 --> 00:04:37,560
all these surveillance cameras

68
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:38,310
can prove it.

69
00:04:38,890 --> 00:04:40,550
Now you should believe me, right?

70
00:04:40,550 --> 00:04:41,070
Sir.

71
00:04:42,780 --> 00:04:43,830
We'll review

72
00:04:44,220 --> 00:04:46,060
every piece of surveillance carefully.

73
00:04:46,060 --> 00:04:47,450
If you're leading the investigation,

74
00:04:47,450 --> 00:04:48,710
I'll fully cooperate.

75
00:04:50,409 --> 00:04:51,210
Alright then.

76
00:04:51,320 --> 00:04:52,580
Let's leave it at that.

77
00:04:53,510 --> 00:04:54,120
By the way,

78
00:04:55,190 --> 00:04:55,990
don't forget—

79
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:57,340
stay in Haizhou

80
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:58,840
for now.

81
00:04:59,220 --> 00:05:00,120
I'll be right here,

82
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,720
ready to assist you anytime.

83
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:02,350
Very good.

84
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:04,240
Zhao.

85
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:04,880
Yes.

86
00:05:05,270 --> 00:05:05,800
Let's go.

87
00:05:05,820 --> 00:05:06,310
Yes.

88
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:22,680
Sir.

89
00:05:25,970 --> 00:05:27,020
This is my report.

90
00:05:31,150 --> 00:05:32,810
I want to check the back alley.

91
00:05:33,210 --> 00:05:34,010
What's wrong?

92
00:05:34,310 --> 00:05:35,710
I still don't understand

93
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:36,830
why

94
00:05:36,830 --> 00:05:40,030
Lai Zhengtian knew
police were following him yesterday.

95
00:05:41,620 --> 00:05:42,220
Zhao Ping.

96
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:45,280
Chief Tan.

97
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:48,190
Go with your senior
to check the back alley.

98
00:05:48,190 --> 00:05:48,600
Yes.

99
00:05:48,730 --> 00:05:49,260
Go ahead.

100
00:06:00,390 --> 00:06:00,920
Cheng,

101
00:06:01,010 --> 00:06:02,610
let me propose a toast to you.

102
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:11,590
Officer Zhou, can't bear to leave me?

103
00:06:11,590 --> 00:06:13,580
You just left and now you're back again.

104
00:06:13,580 --> 00:06:14,580
Working on a case.

105
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:15,920
Need my help?

106
00:06:16,180 --> 00:06:16,910
No need.

107
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:22,870
Senior!

108
00:07:24,410 --> 00:07:26,060
The weather is so unpredictable.

109
00:07:26,060 --> 00:07:27,920
It starts raining out of nowhere.

110
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:31,160
What are you thinking about?

111
00:07:32,550 --> 00:07:33,950
There are police indeed.

112
00:07:38,390 --> 00:07:39,030
"Indeed."

113
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:42,560
Lai,

114
00:07:42,830 --> 00:07:44,150
there are cops here.

115
00:07:47,980 --> 00:07:48,830
Out on duty?

116
00:07:50,750 --> 00:07:53,010
I know police tactics better than you do.

117
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:58,430
I've thought of a lead,

118
00:07:58,760 --> 00:07:59,890
but I'm not sure yet.

119
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,560
You really have been

120
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:02,690
badly traumatized.

121
00:08:03,100 --> 00:08:04,670
Not to criticize you, Senior,

122
00:08:04,670 --> 00:08:06,600
but could you stop making us worry?

123
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:08,200
If it weren't for Professor Jiang
yesterday,

124
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:10,300
you would've ended up
in the hospital again.

125
00:08:10,300 --> 00:08:12,130
I haven't properly interrogated you yet.

126
00:08:12,130 --> 00:08:13,370
What's going on?

127
00:08:13,450 --> 00:08:15,310
How did you suddenly get married?

128
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:16,630
Senior, listen.

129
00:08:16,970 --> 00:08:18,530
You never even dated before.

130
00:08:18,530 --> 00:08:20,330
I thought you were afraid of men.

131
00:08:20,350 --> 00:08:22,410
Can you focus on examining the scene?

132
00:08:24,050 --> 00:08:25,370
I am examining it.

133
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,990
Just got carried away talking.

134
00:08:26,990 --> 00:08:28,720
Then keep examining properly.

135
00:08:29,630 --> 00:08:30,870
I'll check if the surveillance footage

136
00:08:30,870 --> 00:08:31,870
has been retrieved.

137
00:08:31,870 --> 00:08:32,270
Okay.

138
00:08:33,549 --> 00:08:34,200
Take the umbrella.

139
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:34,669
No need.

140
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:56,540
What are you doing?

141
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:59,170
Are you dating someone?

142
00:09:00,460 --> 00:09:01,720
None of your business.

143
00:09:03,310 --> 00:09:04,440
Just say you're not.

144
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:05,770
If you say so,

145
00:09:06,270 --> 00:09:07,270
I'll believe you.

146
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:08,960
I'm married.

147
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:13,910
Jin,

148
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:15,410
you're messing with me.

149
00:09:15,760 --> 00:09:16,750
I'm not.

150
00:09:17,650 --> 00:09:18,780
I'm really married.

151
00:09:19,910 --> 00:09:21,120
He's a good man.

152
00:09:22,430 --> 00:09:23,360
Better than you.

153
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:33,460
Jiang Cheng, have you lost your mind?

154
00:09:50,070 --> 00:09:51,070
Who did you marry?

155
00:09:52,510 --> 00:09:53,910
That man from last night,

156
00:09:54,630 --> 00:09:55,300
isn't it?

157
00:09:59,240 --> 00:09:59,970
Jiang Cheng,

158
00:10:00,920 --> 00:10:03,180
I really appreciate the life I'm living.

159
00:10:04,110 --> 00:10:05,570
I hope you won't disturb me

160
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:08,080
and my family.

161
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:12,240
Family?

162
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:33,160
By the way,

163
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,120
last night,

164
00:10:35,830 --> 00:10:37,960
it was you who told that person, right?

165
00:10:38,370 --> 00:10:40,170
That the police were following?

166
00:11:13,940 --> 00:11:15,670
You don't need to deny it anymore.

167
00:11:15,670 --> 00:11:16,840
We know exactly

168
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:18,490
what happened at the scene.

169
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:22,840
How long have you been doing this?

170
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:23,970
How did you two meet?

171
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:26,380
We met while drinking.

172
00:11:26,740 --> 00:11:29,220
But I really liked him.

173
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:32,220
Did you know Jiang Cheng had drugs on him?

174
00:11:32,510 --> 00:11:33,320
No way.

175
00:11:34,390 --> 00:11:35,850
Isn't he a police officer?

176
00:11:37,770 --> 00:11:38,500
Jiang Cheng.

177
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:45,220
I don't believe you would hide drugs.

178
00:11:46,550 --> 00:11:48,280
Is someone trying to frame you?

179
00:11:51,030 --> 00:11:51,890
Say something.

180
00:11:55,250 --> 00:11:56,980
I'll believe whatever you say.

181
00:11:58,510 --> 00:11:59,390
Say something.

182
00:12:02,460 --> 00:12:04,000
Did someone set you up?

183
00:12:09,300 --> 00:12:11,060
When did you become like this?

184
00:12:16,070 --> 00:12:17,710
How could I not know at all?

185
00:12:22,740 --> 00:12:24,140
If there's nothing else,

186
00:12:25,060 --> 00:12:26,720
let's leave it at that for now.

187
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:51,560
[Deputy Captain of the Criminal Investigation Brigade
of Fengzhou District, Haizhou City, Binjiang Province]

188
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:57,000
Come in.

189
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:02,240
Sir,

190
00:13:02,270 --> 00:13:03,400
you wanted to see me?

191
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,260
There's new evidence.

192
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:13,840
The forensics lab

193
00:13:14,750 --> 00:13:15,960
needs someone to follow up.

194
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:16,820
Go check it out.

195
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:18,000
Yes.

196
00:13:18,550 --> 00:13:19,840
Professor Jiang is there too.

197
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:20,500
From now on,

198
00:13:21,030 --> 00:13:23,830
you'll be responsible
for coordinating with him.

199
00:13:28,790 --> 00:13:30,190
Is there something else?

200
00:13:33,540 --> 00:13:34,420
Sir...

201
00:13:36,750 --> 00:13:38,020
There's something

202
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:40,780
I need to inform you about.

203
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:42,650
Go ahead.

204
00:13:45,680 --> 00:13:46,700
Phoenix Fire...

205
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:51,850
Jiang Cheng from Phoenix Fire…

206
00:13:53,550 --> 00:13:54,840
He…

207
00:13:58,030 --> 00:13:59,770
He was my…

208
00:14:03,710 --> 00:14:04,920
My ex.

209
00:14:05,270 --> 00:14:06,000
Boyfriend.

210
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:06,630
No,

211
00:14:06,660 --> 00:14:07,470
ex-boyfriend.

212
00:14:07,470 --> 00:14:08,540
Ex-boyfriend.

213
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:10,850
So you already knew?

214
00:14:11,510 --> 00:14:12,510
I was just waiting

215
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:14,720
to see when you'd tell me.

216
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:16,600
Sir,

217
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:19,060
I have absolutely no relationship
with him now.

218
00:14:19,060 --> 00:14:20,120
I promise his presence

219
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:21,480
won't affect my work at all.

220
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:22,690
Yes, you don't need to be so nervous.

221
00:14:22,690 --> 00:14:23,890
No one is blaming you.

222
00:14:25,420 --> 00:14:26,030
Actually,

223
00:14:26,910 --> 00:14:28,070
that day in the storage room,

224
00:14:28,070 --> 00:14:29,910
he was the one who led the attack.

225
00:14:34,270 --> 00:14:35,480
Working under He Wu

226
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:37,010
and reaching his position,

227
00:14:38,550 --> 00:14:40,480
he can't be a good person.

228
00:14:41,550 --> 00:14:42,750
And I've noticed

229
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:44,540
that the way he looks at you

230
00:14:46,630 --> 00:14:47,750
isn't pure.

231
00:14:48,240 --> 00:14:48,790
So,

232
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:50,480
from now on,

233
00:14:51,270 --> 00:14:53,530
you should go to Phoenix Fire less often.

234
00:14:54,150 --> 00:14:54,550
Okay.

235
00:14:55,150 --> 00:14:55,950
You can go now.

236
00:15:32,270 --> 00:15:33,270
Professor Jiang.

237
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:37,160
What's wrong?

238
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:37,770
Nothing.

239
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:39,980
Have you eaten?

240
00:15:40,510 --> 00:15:41,370
I'm not hungry.

241
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:43,970
I haven't eaten yet.

242
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:45,260
Let's go together.

243
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:48,600
Didn't you say
there was some new progress?

244
00:15:49,870 --> 00:15:51,870
We need to wait for the results
from the tech department.

245
00:15:51,870 --> 00:15:53,270
We'll have answers soon.

246
00:15:55,030 --> 00:15:56,490
Can you handle spicy food?

247
00:15:56,550 --> 00:15:58,950
There's a good Sichuan restaurant nearby.

248
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:00,620
We can get takeout from there.

249
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:01,960
We go there often.

250
00:16:02,560 --> 00:16:03,890
I'm fine with anything.

251
00:16:04,320 --> 00:16:04,670
Okay.

252
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:10,630
Dan,

253
00:16:10,960 --> 00:16:11,930
do you want some Sichuan food?

254
00:16:11,930 --> 00:16:13,200
I can bring you some takeout.

255
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:14,670
There are quite a few people today.

256
00:16:14,670 --> 00:16:16,030
About eight or nine people.

257
00:16:16,030 --> 00:16:16,790
No problem.

258
00:16:16,840 --> 00:16:18,370
Someone's treating today.

259
00:16:18,390 --> 00:16:20,910
I know who's paying.

260
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:22,140
Nine portions in total.

261
00:16:22,140 --> 00:16:23,320
Thank you for your kindness.

262
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:24,920
Thank you, Professor Jiang.

263
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:25,600
Just wait.

264
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:33,890
Let's go.

265
00:16:34,870 --> 00:16:35,400
Zhou Jin.

266
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:37,880
What's wrong?

267
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:39,510
You lost a button.

268
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:57,000
I don't even know how it fell off.

269
00:17:02,530 --> 00:17:03,990
Be more careful next time.

270
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:16,480
Right there!

271
00:17:16,790 --> 00:17:17,720
That's perfect!

272
00:17:18,730 --> 00:17:21,440
A-After you finish massaging my back,

273
00:17:21,730 --> 00:17:23,260
please massage my head too.

274
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:26,380
My head hurts
from drinking too much yesterday.

275
00:17:44,310 --> 00:17:44,840
Brother,

276
00:17:45,750 --> 00:17:46,210
it's me.

277
00:18:01,070 --> 00:18:03,310
Jiang Cheng, are you crazy?

278
00:18:03,550 --> 00:18:04,610
What are you doing?

279
00:18:05,970 --> 00:18:07,370
I'm here to take someone.

280
00:18:08,350 --> 00:18:09,190
I'm taking Da Mao

281
00:18:09,190 --> 00:18:10,040
with me.

282
00:18:10,790 --> 00:18:13,310
He's Lai's man.
What right do you have to take him?

283
00:18:13,310 --> 00:18:14,880
Lai San is about to get shot,

284
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:16,530
yet you're still showing off?

285
00:18:16,530 --> 00:18:18,680
From now on, what I say goes.

286
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:19,850
Don't waste my time!

287
00:18:21,210 --> 00:18:22,450
He's blind anyway.

288
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:23,850
What use is he to you?

289
00:18:27,260 --> 00:18:28,800
You're the one who blinded him!

290
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:29,730
Well, that's...

291
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:35,400
Cheng,

292
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:39,260
I respect that you've come out on top.

293
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:42,960
Let's cut the crap.

294
00:18:43,590 --> 00:18:44,880
I won't hold it against you

295
00:18:44,880 --> 00:18:46,120
about what happened a year ago.

296
00:18:46,120 --> 00:18:47,250
I'm taking him with me.

297
00:18:47,250 --> 00:18:50,450
If you want to blame someone,
blame Lai for being useless.

298
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:54,000
Count it.

299
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:56,130
Don't say I don't follow the rules.

300
00:18:56,550 --> 00:18:57,080
Xiao Mao,

301
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:58,730
take your brother home.

302
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:07,560
This is the place.

303
00:19:15,790 --> 00:19:16,270
Zhang.

304
00:19:17,310 --> 00:19:18,840
Officer Zhou, you're here.

305
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,460
What would you like today?

306
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:21,350
The usual.

307
00:19:21,550 --> 00:19:24,030
Two meat and two vegetable dishes,
nine portions. Deliver them to the team.

308
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:25,180
Then bring the menu over.

309
00:19:25,180 --> 00:19:25,880
We're eating here.

310
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:26,440
Alright.

311
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:28,720
Take a look first.

312
00:19:34,750 --> 00:19:35,750
Professor Jiang.

313
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:37,880
If my habit is

314
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:39,680
to order four dishes,

315
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:41,800
split them into three portions,

316
00:19:41,890 --> 00:19:43,550
and eat them over three meals,

317
00:19:43,920 --> 00:19:44,780
would you mind?

318
00:19:46,270 --> 00:19:46,800
Zhou Jin.

319
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:48,770
My salary is decent.

320
00:19:49,190 --> 00:19:50,110
You don't need to be so frugal.

321
00:19:50,110 --> 00:19:51,400
It's not about saving money.

322
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:53,130
I just don't want to waste food.

323
00:19:53,960 --> 00:19:55,000
Can we discuss this?

324
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,110
Of course we can.

325
00:19:56,550 --> 00:19:58,440
You're the godsend to our team.

326
00:19:58,750 --> 00:20:01,150
Even Sir
keeps talking about you every day.

327
00:20:01,310 --> 00:20:03,200
So I need to make sure
you're properly settled in.

328
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:04,220
Food is the first necessity of the people.

329
00:20:04,220 --> 00:20:05,550
And you are my priority.

330
00:20:05,750 --> 00:20:08,170
I think ordering three dishes
would be just right.

331
00:20:08,170 --> 00:20:09,430
I have a good appetite.

332
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:10,350
Zhou Jin,

333
00:20:11,200 --> 00:20:12,460
there are two of us now.

334
00:20:15,350 --> 00:20:15,880
Okay.

335
00:20:46,710 --> 00:20:48,310
Here's the Kung Pao Chicken!

336
00:20:49,560 --> 00:20:50,360
Officer Zhou,

337
00:20:50,590 --> 00:20:51,590
you're here.

338
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:53,920
Where are the other officers
from your team?

339
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:54,920
They're all busy.

340
00:20:55,480 --> 00:20:57,480
So you've officially started working?

341
00:20:57,480 --> 00:20:58,880
How have you been lately?

342
00:21:02,790 --> 00:21:04,000
I've really quit.

343
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:05,270
Officer Zhou,

344
00:21:05,510 --> 00:21:06,240
don't worry.

345
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:07,700
I don't have any cravings at all.

346
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:08,430
That's good.

347
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:10,080
You look much healthier now.

348
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:12,090
And you have a good complexion too.

349
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:14,510
This officer looks unfamiliar.

350
00:21:14,590 --> 00:21:16,070
I haven't seen him before, right?

351
00:21:16,070 --> 00:21:16,920
This is...

352
00:21:17,510 --> 00:21:18,440
He is...

353
00:21:19,510 --> 00:21:21,370
He's Professor Jiang, a teacher.

354
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:24,660
I see. Nice to meet you, Professor Jiang.

355
00:21:24,670 --> 00:21:25,550
Nice to meet you.

356
00:21:25,550 --> 00:21:27,530
I'll ask the kitchen
to prepare a Sichuan Boiled Fish.

357
00:21:27,530 --> 00:21:28,860
Have some before you go.

358
00:21:29,680 --> 00:21:32,240
No need. Officer Zhou
is sensitive to fishy smells.

359
00:21:32,240 --> 00:21:33,350
She doesn't like fish.

360
00:21:33,350 --> 00:21:34,670
Alright then, take your time and chat.

361
00:21:34,670 --> 00:21:36,400
I'll go back to the kitchen now.

362
00:21:39,030 --> 00:21:41,630
How did you know
I'm sensitive to fishy smells?

363
00:21:52,270 --> 00:21:53,640
Bai Yang, what's up?

364
00:21:54,110 --> 00:21:55,550
Is Professor Jiang with you?

365
00:21:55,550 --> 00:21:56,150
Yes, he is.

366
00:21:56,680 --> 00:21:58,740
Tell him he's absolutely brilliant.

367
00:21:58,830 --> 00:21:59,880
Following his instructions,

368
00:21:59,880 --> 00:22:01,750
I checked all the ride-hailing services
and illegal taxis

369
00:22:01,750 --> 00:22:03,200
that passed through Tonghe riverside
and used the Haiji Highway

370
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:04,350
around the time of the incident.

371
00:22:04,350 --> 00:22:05,440
Haiji Highway?

372
00:22:05,830 --> 00:22:06,630
That's right.

373
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:08,550
Honglian County is Meng Ling's hometown.

374
00:22:08,550 --> 00:22:10,920
If Meng Ling wanted
to return to Honglian from Haizhou,

375
00:22:10,920 --> 00:22:11,750
then the Haiji Highway

376
00:22:11,750 --> 00:22:13,610
would be the route she had to take.

377
00:22:14,070 --> 00:22:15,720
So she booked a ride in advance

378
00:22:15,720 --> 00:22:16,980
but never made it home.

379
00:22:17,070 --> 00:22:18,270
Yes, very likely.

380
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:21,000
There's a van that operates
as an unlicensed taxi.

381
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:22,680
It was at the Tonghe riverside
on the night of the incident,

382
00:22:22,680 --> 00:22:25,030
and it frequently travels
between Honglian and Haizhou.

383
00:22:25,030 --> 00:22:26,160
Can we find this van?

384
00:22:26,690 --> 00:22:27,620
It's in the city.

385
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,680
How did you come up with this?

386
00:22:30,310 --> 00:22:31,770
Professor Jiang analyzed

387
00:22:31,790 --> 00:22:33,200
that if Lai San had premeditated

388
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:34,200
to kill Meng Ling,

389
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:36,550
he wouldn't have used a standard gun.

390
00:22:36,550 --> 00:22:37,720
Meng Ling was so frail.

391
00:22:37,720 --> 00:22:39,590
He could have used a more common weapon.

392
00:22:39,590 --> 00:22:41,200
And he wouldn't need to do it himself.

393
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:42,550
Also, from the surveillance footage,

394
00:22:42,550 --> 00:22:43,510
when Meng Ling went to meet someone,

395
00:22:43,510 --> 00:22:45,720
she didn't show any signs of tension
or anxiety.

396
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:46,550
Lai San's action

397
00:22:46,550 --> 00:22:48,070
was likely a crime of passion.

398
00:22:48,070 --> 00:22:51,530
Meng Ling actually had a real chance
to return to her hometown.

399
00:22:52,250 --> 00:22:54,000
Okay, I'll get Zhao Ping
to track the van.

400
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:56,260
Send him the license plate and location.

401
00:22:56,480 --> 00:22:57,160
Got it.

402
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:02,000
Professor Jiang,

403
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:03,670
Bai Yang did as you said

404
00:23:03,830 --> 00:23:04,680
and found the clue.

405
00:23:04,680 --> 00:23:06,110
So this is the result
you wanted us to wait for,

406
00:23:06,110 --> 00:23:06,790
isn't it?

407
00:23:10,240 --> 00:23:11,840
Bring that person back to me.

408
00:23:13,720 --> 00:23:14,460
When did this idea

409
00:23:14,460 --> 00:23:15,540
first come to you?

410
00:23:16,750 --> 00:23:17,480
Yesterday.

411
00:23:18,160 --> 00:23:19,670
Then why didn't you tell me

412
00:23:19,750 --> 00:23:21,000
when I asked

413
00:23:21,350 --> 00:23:23,550
if you had anything to add this morning?

414
00:23:23,550 --> 00:23:25,750
I wanted to wait
until I had results to tell you.

415
00:23:25,750 --> 00:23:26,880
But we're partners.

416
00:23:27,790 --> 00:23:30,110
Shouldn't partners
tell each other everything?

417
00:23:30,110 --> 00:23:32,310
Even though I'm happy with this result,

418
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:34,440
I don't like

419
00:23:34,880 --> 00:23:36,480
being kept in the dark

420
00:23:36,920 --> 00:23:37,550
like this.

421
00:23:38,510 --> 00:23:39,710
We're just partners?

422
00:23:40,550 --> 00:23:43,010
You're the expert
and I'm here to assist you.

423
00:23:43,020 --> 00:23:44,190
I can learn from you,

424
00:23:44,640 --> 00:23:45,940
but I need to be kept in the loop

425
00:23:45,940 --> 00:23:47,070
and give my consent.

426
00:23:47,310 --> 00:23:49,040
That's called mutual respect.

427
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:52,860
I understand what you mean.

428
00:23:52,860 --> 00:23:54,120
It won't happen again.

429
00:23:54,310 --> 00:23:54,910
I'm sorry.

430
00:23:56,270 --> 00:23:56,960
Never mind.

431
00:23:57,230 --> 00:23:58,010
Professor Jiang,

432
00:23:58,010 --> 00:23:59,070
let's keep eating.

433
00:24:10,960 --> 00:24:11,880
Did you choke?

434
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:17,210
Zhou Jin,

435
00:24:18,050 --> 00:24:19,450
this is really too spicy.

436
00:24:20,070 --> 00:24:20,680
Spicy?

437
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:23,320
Can't you handle spicy food?

438
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:26,300
Why didn't you tell me?

439
00:24:27,590 --> 00:24:28,240
I'm sorry.

440
00:24:29,270 --> 00:24:30,400
I'm not blaming you.

441
00:24:31,850 --> 00:24:32,570
I remember

442
00:24:33,110 --> 00:24:33,780
you like it.

443
00:24:38,160 --> 00:24:38,800
Jin,

444
00:24:38,830 --> 00:24:40,090
why aren't you eating?

445
00:24:40,250 --> 00:24:41,620
How could she handle this stuff?

446
00:24:41,220 --> 00:24:43,960
[2002]

447
00:24:42,350 --> 00:24:43,350
She insisted on coming along.

448
00:24:43,350 --> 00:24:44,480
Feeling stupid now?

449
00:24:44,760 --> 00:24:45,620
I can handle it.

450
00:24:48,500 --> 00:24:50,680
Jiang Cheng, look—
Jin got hit by the spice.

451
00:24:50,680 --> 00:24:52,800
Why are you overestimating yourself?

452
00:24:52,800 --> 00:24:54,590
Who said that? I love spicy food.

453
00:24:54,590 --> 00:24:55,510
I just choked earlier,

454
00:24:55,510 --> 00:24:56,440
got it?

455
00:24:59,960 --> 00:25:01,360
I don't like it that much.

456
00:25:01,830 --> 00:25:03,340
We can try
a different restaurant next time.

457
00:25:03,340 --> 00:25:04,100
I'm fine.

458
00:25:08,030 --> 00:25:09,160
But I'm not.

459
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:11,480
Professor Jiang,

460
00:25:12,750 --> 00:25:14,410
I don't want you to compromise

461
00:25:14,440 --> 00:25:15,770
just to accommodate me.

462
00:25:16,310 --> 00:25:17,750
You can just tell me what you like

463
00:25:17,750 --> 00:25:18,880
and what you don't.

464
00:25:19,790 --> 00:25:20,750
From now on, we'll order things

465
00:25:20,750 --> 00:25:22,070
we both enjoy.

466
00:25:24,210 --> 00:25:25,070
How about this?

467
00:25:25,510 --> 00:25:27,440
Let's order some non-spicy dishes.

468
00:25:27,440 --> 00:25:28,480
I'll take these home

469
00:25:28,480 --> 00:25:29,810
for a late-night snack.

470
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:31,810
It's up to you.

471
00:25:32,640 --> 00:25:33,970
You're so considerate.

472
00:25:38,560 --> 00:25:40,360
Let your brother have some more.

473
00:25:42,700 --> 00:25:43,590
Slow down.

474
00:25:47,310 --> 00:25:48,480
Eat slowly.

475
00:25:49,160 --> 00:25:50,810
After dinner,
take your brother to the boat.

476
00:25:50,810 --> 00:25:52,230
Once you've settled in
at your destination,

477
00:25:52,230 --> 00:25:53,690
remember to give me a call.

478
00:25:54,230 --> 00:25:55,290
Sure thing, Cheng.

479
00:25:58,110 --> 00:25:59,720
This money is for your brother
to open a shop.

480
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:00,830
Don't spend it carelessly,

481
00:26:00,830 --> 00:26:02,360
or I'll twist your head off.

482
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:05,750
Count it yourself when you get there.

483
00:26:05,750 --> 00:26:06,630
There's 50,000 inside.

484
00:26:06,630 --> 00:26:08,110
Don't give any to your younger brother.

485
00:26:08,110 --> 00:26:09,920
Eating is the only thing he's good at.

486
00:26:09,920 --> 00:26:10,680
Alright.

487
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:13,400
Cheng,

488
00:26:13,750 --> 00:26:14,590
my brother

489
00:26:14,660 --> 00:26:15,720
wants to thank you.

490
00:26:17,030 --> 00:26:17,770
If it weren't for

491
00:26:17,770 --> 00:26:19,630
Boss He sending me away back then,

492
00:26:19,720 --> 00:26:22,250
your brother
wouldn't have suffered so much.

493
00:26:22,300 --> 00:26:24,270
It's all because everything
that bastard Lai San did

494
00:26:24,270 --> 00:26:25,400
was inhuman.

495
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:29,930
Now that you're back,
everyone will have better days ahead.

496
00:26:34,790 --> 00:26:35,790
By the way, Cheng,

497
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:38,200
why would Lai San want to kill Meng Ling?

498
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:39,310
How would I know?

499
00:26:39,310 --> 00:26:40,640
He's crazy, that's why.

500
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:42,350
But people are saying

501
00:26:42,790 --> 00:26:44,990
that you turned Lai San in to the police.

502
00:26:45,070 --> 00:26:45,880
Nonsense!

503
00:26:45,950 --> 00:26:47,470
Did I tell him to kill that person?

504
00:26:47,470 --> 00:26:48,540
That's impossible.

505
00:26:48,540 --> 00:26:49,170
Cheng,

506
00:26:49,390 --> 00:26:50,250
you don't know,

507
00:26:50,890 --> 00:26:53,890
Meng Ling has had a terrible time
these past two years.

508
00:27:05,590 --> 00:27:07,520
Enough. Let's not talk about this.

509
00:27:08,290 --> 00:27:09,270
Here, Brother.

510
00:27:22,400 --> 00:27:23,600
What's wrong, Cheng?

511
00:27:25,960 --> 00:27:26,760
It's nothing.

512
00:27:27,030 --> 00:27:28,090
Boss He is back now.

513
00:27:30,550 --> 00:27:31,860
So don't worry anymore.

514
00:27:31,860 --> 00:27:34,320
If the sky falls,
he'll be there to hold it up.

515
00:27:37,750 --> 00:27:38,360
What's up?

516
00:27:56,360 --> 00:27:58,160
This is the password?

517
00:28:03,200 --> 00:28:04,530
For Liu Jinlong's safe?

518
00:28:06,550 --> 00:28:07,240
Wait.

519
00:28:07,750 --> 00:28:09,550
Brother, how did you...

520
00:28:12,160 --> 00:28:13,710
So you're half-blind.

521
00:28:16,420 --> 00:28:17,250
Let me do it.

522
00:28:45,340 --> 00:28:46,780
Jiang Cheng.

523
00:28:48,510 --> 00:28:49,900
Cheng.

524
00:28:58,680 --> 00:28:59,940
I heard from Chief Tan.

525
00:29:00,040 --> 00:29:01,380
Lai Zhengtian has been arrested,

526
00:29:01,380 --> 00:29:02,680
but the gun hasn't been found,

527
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:04,440
and you couldn't get information
about the primary crime scene.

528
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:04,750
That's true.

529
00:29:04,750 --> 00:29:06,920
We're still looking for a breakthrough,

530
00:29:06,920 --> 00:29:08,960
so we want to understand
the specific situation.

531
00:29:08,960 --> 00:29:10,200
Since the municipal bureau
takes this case seriously,

532
00:29:10,200 --> 00:29:11,200
our cooperation is essential.

533
00:29:11,200 --> 00:29:12,130
That's our duty.

534
00:29:12,350 --> 00:29:13,510
I mainly want to know about

535
00:29:13,510 --> 00:29:14,920
the assault case from a year ago.

536
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:15,400
Okay,

537
00:29:15,550 --> 00:29:17,270
let's start from the beginning

538
00:29:17,270 --> 00:29:18,330
and go into detail.

539
00:29:19,030 --> 00:29:19,880
I remember

540
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:22,240
it was the night of June 11th last year

541
00:29:22,240 --> 00:29:23,590
when we received the call.

542
00:29:23,590 --> 00:29:24,720
A resident reported

543
00:29:24,830 --> 00:29:26,480
hearing heart-wrenching screams

544
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:28,920
near Funing Street;

545
00:29:29,410 --> 00:29:30,110
they were truly horrifying.

546
00:29:29,490 --> 00:29:34,280
[2016]

547
00:29:30,960 --> 00:29:32,030
When they went to check,

548
00:29:32,030 --> 00:29:34,200
four or five people
were beating someone up.

549
00:29:34,200 --> 00:29:34,790
Afraid someone might die,

550
00:29:34,790 --> 00:29:36,720
they called the police right away.

551
00:29:41,960 --> 00:29:43,070
Go to hell!

552
00:29:43,720 --> 00:29:45,220
That's for bullying my sister!

553
00:29:45,220 --> 00:29:46,370
Just kill me!

554
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:47,200
I'll kill you!

555
00:29:47,270 --> 00:29:48,480
Just kill me!

556
00:29:48,500 --> 00:29:50,390
Stop hitting me!

557
00:29:51,110 --> 00:29:52,820
The place where they fought

558
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:54,930
was under renovation at that time.

559
00:29:55,020 --> 00:29:55,880
There weren't many people around

560
00:29:55,880 --> 00:29:57,080
and no lights either.

561
00:29:57,240 --> 00:29:58,830
After we received the report,

562
00:29:58,830 --> 00:30:00,830
we arrived at the scene in 10 minutes

563
00:30:00,960 --> 00:30:02,480
and took everyone away.

564
00:30:10,270 --> 00:30:11,000
Are you okay?

565
00:30:11,720 --> 00:30:12,250
I'm fine.

566
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:14,350
The victim was Lai Zhengtian.

567
00:30:14,880 --> 00:30:17,160
His arm was severely injured,

568
00:30:17,440 --> 00:30:18,550
so he was sent to the hospital.

569
00:30:18,550 --> 00:30:20,680
We interrogated the attackers first.

570
00:30:21,310 --> 00:30:21,720
Yes.

571
00:30:22,720 --> 00:30:25,030
The man who led the fight

572
00:30:25,240 --> 00:30:26,300
has the surname Hu.

573
00:30:26,440 --> 00:30:27,700
He has a younger sister

574
00:30:28,030 --> 00:30:31,310
who attended Guoshan Experimental
High School a few years ago.

575
00:30:31,310 --> 00:30:33,750
One night,
after her evening study session,

576
00:30:33,750 --> 00:30:35,030
she ran into Lai Zhengtian

577
00:30:35,030 --> 00:30:36,590
on her way home.

578
00:30:37,510 --> 00:30:39,110
That scumbag Lai Zhengtian

579
00:30:39,510 --> 00:30:40,880
sexually assaulted

580
00:30:41,110 --> 00:30:41,960
the poor girl.

581
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:44,070
The girl was terrified

582
00:30:44,350 --> 00:30:45,950
and didn't dare tell anyone.

583
00:30:46,290 --> 00:30:47,210
Until one day,

584
00:30:47,240 --> 00:30:48,480
she had an emotional breakdown

585
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:49,810
and attempted suicide.

586
00:30:49,880 --> 00:30:51,310
Only then did her family learn

587
00:30:51,310 --> 00:30:52,440
what had happened.

588
00:30:53,180 --> 00:30:54,390
I remember at that time,

589
00:30:54,390 --> 00:30:56,260
he had an arm broken, right?

590
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:57,830
Left arm.

591
00:31:00,720 --> 00:31:02,580
Maybe it wasn't just the left arm.

592
00:31:03,400 --> 00:31:06,030
Was there something else?

593
00:31:07,480 --> 00:31:08,110
Well...

594
00:31:10,790 --> 00:31:12,350
I want to know every detail.

595
00:31:12,860 --> 00:31:14,260
Thanks for cooperating.

596
00:31:17,510 --> 00:31:19,240
It's not that we can't tell you.

597
00:31:19,510 --> 00:31:20,350
It's just

598
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:23,750
really hard to talk about.

599
00:31:27,720 --> 00:31:28,720
To put it simply,

600
00:31:29,270 --> 00:31:30,130
they basically

601
00:31:30,550 --> 00:31:31,480
gave him a taste

602
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:33,010
of his own medicine.

603
00:31:36,810 --> 00:31:37,640
Well,

604
00:31:37,680 --> 00:31:38,790
the girl's brother

605
00:31:39,900 --> 00:31:41,700
used some rather brutal methods

606
00:31:41,940 --> 00:31:43,050
to get revenge.

607
00:31:46,080 --> 00:31:48,200
You're saying Meng Ling knew about this

608
00:31:48,200 --> 00:31:49,330
and mentioned it,

609
00:31:49,370 --> 00:31:51,100
which provoked Lai Zhengtian?

610
00:31:51,150 --> 00:31:52,410
According to our analysis,

611
00:31:52,410 --> 00:31:54,380
Lai Zhengtian
committed a crime of passion.

612
00:31:54,380 --> 00:31:55,640
There must be a reason.

613
00:31:56,040 --> 00:31:58,300
Meng Ling said she had leverage over him.

614
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:00,380
Could it be this incident?

615
00:32:01,230 --> 00:32:02,090
Lai Zhengtian,

616
00:32:02,400 --> 00:32:04,400
with his cousin He Wu as his backing,

617
00:32:04,680 --> 00:32:06,010
had always been a bully.

618
00:32:06,490 --> 00:32:08,090
He was always the aggressor.

619
00:32:08,210 --> 00:32:09,540
But after that night,

620
00:32:09,750 --> 00:32:11,280
he was not only victimized,

621
00:32:11,350 --> 00:32:13,470
but also couldn't even bring himself
to speak of his suffering.

622
00:32:13,470 --> 00:32:15,630
It was absolutely a profound humiliation.

623
00:32:15,630 --> 00:32:16,270
So that was

624
00:32:16,300 --> 00:32:18,160
a major trauma for Lai Zhengtian.

625
00:32:18,510 --> 00:32:19,220
That's why

626
00:32:19,250 --> 00:32:21,380
he recklessly shot someone.

627
00:32:21,590 --> 00:32:22,640
It's not the only explanation,

628
00:32:22,640 --> 00:32:24,300
but it's significant enough.

629
00:32:24,310 --> 00:32:26,240
And I heard in Hongyun's testimony

630
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:28,140
that after Jiang Cheng...

631
00:32:34,570 --> 00:32:36,370
After Jiang Cheng left Haizhou,

632
00:32:36,560 --> 00:32:38,270
Lai Zhengtian, out of revenge,

633
00:32:38,270 --> 00:32:39,110
subjected Meng Ling

634
00:32:39,110 --> 00:32:41,280
to various forms of abuse for a long time.

635
00:32:41,280 --> 00:32:41,930
Yes.

636
00:32:42,460 --> 00:32:44,460
From a psychological perspective,

637
00:32:44,470 --> 00:32:46,400
this strong tendency toward abuse

638
00:32:46,450 --> 00:32:48,450
may stem from various motivations,

639
00:32:48,610 --> 00:32:49,470
but typically,

640
00:32:49,920 --> 00:32:52,850
it's about releasing
uncontrollable primal urges.

641
00:32:55,860 --> 00:32:57,790
That person is Jiang Cheng, right?

642
00:32:59,050 --> 00:33:00,510
It was just a chance encounter,

643
00:33:00,510 --> 00:33:02,030
and then

644
00:33:02,310 --> 00:33:04,240
some unpleasant things happened.

645
00:33:04,340 --> 00:33:05,940
I'm heading to Phoenix Fire.

646
00:33:06,580 --> 00:33:07,170
Zhou Jin.

647
00:33:08,100 --> 00:33:09,100
You lost a button.

648
00:33:11,960 --> 00:33:13,760
I don't even know how it fell off.

649
00:33:15,750 --> 00:33:16,680
Jiang Hansheng.

650
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:20,000
What I mean is,

651
00:33:20,770 --> 00:33:22,870
given Lai Zhengtian's
current physical state

652
00:33:22,870 --> 00:33:24,400
and his past with Meng Ling,

653
00:33:24,750 --> 00:33:26,310
even if he didn't shoot because of this,

654
00:33:26,310 --> 00:33:27,400
it would be enough to break down

655
00:33:27,400 --> 00:33:28,790
his mental defenses.

656
00:33:29,110 --> 00:33:30,390
I agree with your point.

657
00:33:30,390 --> 00:33:32,350
You can try it during the interrogation.

658
00:33:32,350 --> 00:33:32,920
Great!

659
00:33:34,220 --> 00:33:35,170
I'll go try it then.

660
00:33:35,170 --> 00:33:35,780
Zhou Jin,

661
00:33:36,240 --> 00:33:37,990
once Lai Zhengtian mentally breaks down,

662
00:33:37,990 --> 00:33:39,990
he might exhibit extreme behavior.

663
00:33:39,990 --> 00:33:41,650
Let Chief Tan know about this.

664
00:33:44,150 --> 00:33:44,950
I understand.

665
00:33:47,720 --> 00:33:49,320
Are you coming home tonight?

666
00:33:49,550 --> 00:33:50,790
I probably won't make it back.

667
00:33:50,790 --> 00:33:51,640
If it gets late,

668
00:33:51,640 --> 00:33:53,170
I'll sleep in the duty dorm.

669
00:33:54,200 --> 00:33:54,590
Okay.

670
00:33:58,070 --> 00:33:58,680
Zhou Jin.

671
00:34:00,640 --> 00:34:01,240
What is it?

672
00:34:02,400 --> 00:34:03,330
Where did you put

673
00:34:03,350 --> 00:34:04,410
your wedding ring?

674
00:34:06,510 --> 00:34:07,440
It's at my place.

675
00:34:09,489 --> 00:34:11,690
Why are you suddenly asking about this?

676
00:34:11,760 --> 00:34:13,620
Nothing. Carry on with your work.

677
00:34:38,469 --> 00:34:39,350
Where did you go

678
00:34:39,370 --> 00:34:41,370
on the 23rd and 24th?

679
00:34:41,400 --> 00:34:41,920
Who did you meet?

680
00:34:41,920 --> 00:34:42,440
What did you eat?

681
00:34:42,440 --> 00:34:43,360
What did you drink?

682
00:34:43,360 --> 00:34:45,760
You'd better recall everything right now.

683
00:34:45,760 --> 00:34:46,590
We've already found out

684
00:34:46,590 --> 00:34:48,110
you weren't home that day at all.

685
00:34:48,110 --> 00:34:49,370
Tell us where you went.

686
00:34:51,670 --> 00:34:52,530
Lai Zhengtian!

687
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:54,540
I'm talking to you.

688
00:34:56,070 --> 00:34:57,910
Why so loud? You startled me.

689
00:34:58,340 --> 00:34:59,270
Why don't you guess?

690
00:34:59,270 --> 00:35:01,270
This guy can really drag things out.

691
00:35:01,300 --> 00:35:03,560
If he didn't have grudges with Meng Ling,

692
00:35:03,610 --> 00:35:05,670
I'd wonder if we got the wrong person.

693
00:35:07,670 --> 00:35:09,230
Coffee's here.

694
00:35:09,230 --> 00:35:10,690
Thanks for your hard work.

695
00:35:10,840 --> 00:35:12,230
Thank you.

696
00:35:19,800 --> 00:35:20,530
Thanks, Dan.

697
00:35:22,920 --> 00:35:23,840
Smells good.

698
00:35:25,030 --> 00:35:26,090
Here, take a sniff.

699
00:35:30,210 --> 00:35:32,670
Any new instructions from Professor Jiang?

700
00:35:39,800 --> 00:35:40,660
Actually, yes.

701
00:35:42,270 --> 00:35:42,750
Dan,

702
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:43,880
come in with me.

703
00:35:44,190 --> 00:35:44,850
In a moment,

704
00:35:44,930 --> 00:35:46,470
I'll handle the questioning,

705
00:35:46,470 --> 00:35:47,930
and you just need to smile.

706
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:48,510
Smile?

707
00:35:49,710 --> 00:35:51,370
What's that supposed to mean?

708
00:35:53,070 --> 00:35:54,230
I want you

709
00:35:54,780 --> 00:35:55,840
to look down on him.

710
00:35:57,060 --> 00:35:59,060
Show him pure contempt from a woman.

711
00:36:06,130 --> 00:36:06,590
Mr. Wan,

712
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:08,130
let me take over for you.

713
00:36:19,220 --> 00:36:19,950
Look.

714
00:36:20,850 --> 00:36:22,840
If they had sent you two
to keep me company earlier,

715
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:24,500
I wouldn't have been so bored.

716
00:36:25,380 --> 00:36:26,290
Maybe

717
00:36:26,710 --> 00:36:27,800
if you cheer me up,

718
00:36:27,800 --> 00:36:29,400
I might remember something.

719
00:36:29,890 --> 00:36:30,880
Do you remember me?

720
00:36:30,880 --> 00:36:31,710
Of course I do.

721
00:36:32,570 --> 00:36:33,500
Absolutely.

722
00:36:34,310 --> 00:36:35,660
You're quite a catch.

723
00:36:35,880 --> 00:36:37,940
Why did you end up in this profession?

724
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:39,800
If you worked for me,

725
00:36:40,070 --> 00:36:41,130
I would definitely

726
00:36:41,510 --> 00:36:42,550
turn you into

727
00:36:42,880 --> 00:36:44,760
the most famous princess.

728
00:36:45,400 --> 00:36:47,060
So many men would fall for you.

729
00:36:47,480 --> 00:36:48,710
The market right now

730
00:36:49,010 --> 00:36:50,610
is missing someone like you.

731
00:36:51,440 --> 00:36:52,840
Do you know where you are?

732
00:36:53,070 --> 00:36:54,230
No sense of fun.

733
00:36:55,440 --> 00:36:56,590
What type am I?

734
00:36:58,840 --> 00:36:59,900
A little spitfire.

735
00:37:00,590 --> 00:37:02,230
I have a good eye for people.

736
00:37:02,710 --> 00:37:03,550
Look at you,

737
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:04,900
pretty face,

738
00:37:05,610 --> 00:37:06,540
long neck,

739
00:37:06,630 --> 00:37:07,590
broad shoulders,

740
00:37:07,590 --> 00:37:08,510
tiny waist.

741
00:37:08,880 --> 00:37:10,340
You look best in a uniform.

742
00:37:10,840 --> 00:37:11,840
If you work with me

743
00:37:11,840 --> 00:37:13,100
and learn a few tricks,

744
00:37:13,510 --> 00:37:15,510
you'd have men falling at your feet.

745
00:37:16,290 --> 00:37:17,820
In one night,

746
00:37:18,760 --> 00:37:20,400
you'd make more

747
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:22,200
than a cop makes in a whole month.

748
00:37:22,240 --> 00:37:23,570
So what you're saying is

749
00:37:24,100 --> 00:37:25,760
all the people working for you

750
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:27,800
were personally trained by you?

751
00:37:28,760 --> 00:37:30,360
Was Meng Ling one of them too?

752
00:37:36,240 --> 00:37:37,550
I'm very picky.

753
00:37:38,840 --> 00:37:40,370
I'm only interested in you.

754
00:37:53,890 --> 00:37:55,220
What are you looking at?

755
00:38:05,880 --> 00:38:07,280
What are you laughing at?

756
00:38:09,590 --> 00:38:10,880
As police officers,

757
00:38:10,920 --> 00:38:12,120
we investigate cases

758
00:38:13,110 --> 00:38:14,510
over and over again.

759
00:38:15,110 --> 00:38:17,000
We found a case from a year ago.

760
00:38:20,400 --> 00:38:21,230
I heard

761
00:38:22,320 --> 00:38:23,620
you were in the hospital

762
00:38:23,620 --> 00:38:25,140
for a long time back then.

763
00:38:25,920 --> 00:38:26,450
How is it?

764
00:38:27,510 --> 00:38:28,440
Is your left hand

765
00:38:29,230 --> 00:38:30,000
better now?

766
00:38:30,420 --> 00:38:32,750
What does this have to do
with my left hand?

767
00:38:41,280 --> 00:38:42,740
What are you saying to her?

768
00:38:43,610 --> 00:38:45,010
What are you laughing at?

769
00:38:47,920 --> 00:38:48,640
Chief Tan.

770
00:38:48,660 --> 00:38:50,120
What are you saying to her?

771
00:38:50,760 --> 00:38:52,420
Hey, what are you laughing at?

772
00:38:53,320 --> 00:38:55,050
Hey, what are you saying to her?

773
00:38:55,070 --> 00:38:56,760
What is Zhou Jin doing in there?

774
00:38:56,760 --> 00:38:57,420
Get her out.

775
00:38:58,030 --> 00:38:58,630
Chief Tan,

776
00:38:59,150 --> 00:39:00,210
let's wait and see.

777
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:02,550
Lai Zhengtian has finally started talking.

778
00:39:02,550 --> 00:39:03,680
This is a good start.

779
00:39:04,070 --> 00:39:04,670
Yes.

780
00:39:48,480 --> 00:39:51,210
Let me share some scientific knowledge
with you.

781
00:39:51,710 --> 00:39:53,110
A person's experiences,

782
00:39:54,150 --> 00:39:55,840
especially traumatic ones,

783
00:39:56,410 --> 00:39:57,430
can have a profound impact

784
00:39:57,430 --> 00:39:59,430
on their thought patterns

785
00:40:00,030 --> 00:40:01,620
and behavioral habits.

786
00:40:02,030 --> 00:40:03,440
So what is trauma?

787
00:40:04,850 --> 00:40:05,880
I made notes before.

788
00:40:05,880 --> 00:40:07,210
Let me look it up for you.

789
00:40:07,480 --> 00:40:08,710
It will be helpful for you.

790
00:40:08,710 --> 00:40:10,330
I'm definitely not trying to fool you.

791
00:40:10,330 --> 00:40:11,250
Let me find it.

792
00:40:12,670 --> 00:40:14,070
Here, listen carefully.

793
00:40:14,800 --> 00:40:15,760
Trauma

794
00:40:16,280 --> 00:40:17,540
is generally caused by

795
00:40:18,010 --> 00:40:19,490
external factors

796
00:40:19,920 --> 00:40:21,110
and results in

797
00:40:21,400 --> 00:40:22,860
damage to the body or mind.

798
00:40:23,460 --> 00:40:26,380
It is an automatic physiological

799
00:40:26,610 --> 00:40:29,090
and neurological response
of the individual

800
00:40:29,090 --> 00:40:31,450
to overwhelming events or experiences,

801
00:40:31,700 --> 00:40:32,840
which in turn produces

802
00:40:32,840 --> 00:40:34,240
psychological effects.

803
00:40:35,230 --> 00:40:36,800
Psychological trauma

804
00:40:37,590 --> 00:40:38,650
can be divided into

805
00:40:38,920 --> 00:40:41,520
non-interpersonal and interpersonal types.

806
00:40:42,030 --> 00:40:43,590
Today we'll mainly discuss

807
00:40:43,890 --> 00:40:44,950
interpersonal trauma,

808
00:40:44,950 --> 00:40:46,620
which occurs between people.

809
00:40:48,240 --> 00:40:49,360
For example,

810
00:40:50,380 --> 00:40:51,990
when a loved one dies,

811
00:40:52,630 --> 00:40:54,490
when your girlfriend leaves you,

812
00:40:54,920 --> 00:40:56,990
when your brother betrays you,

813
00:40:57,390 --> 00:40:59,350
when you suffer a violent attack,

814
00:40:59,510 --> 00:41:00,590
or perhaps—

815
00:41:07,480 --> 00:41:09,880
What happened to you a year ago

816
00:41:10,930 --> 00:41:12,980
on Funing Street in Guoshan District?

817
00:41:12,980 --> 00:41:13,730
Wretch!

818
00:41:15,120 --> 00:41:16,910
Don't tell me Meng Ling knows everything

819
00:41:16,910 --> 00:41:18,140
like I do.

820
00:41:20,360 --> 00:41:21,110
My God!

821
00:41:21,460 --> 00:41:22,650
What did she tell you

822
00:41:22,850 --> 00:41:24,090
that made you so angry

823
00:41:24,120 --> 00:41:25,410
and so furious?

824
00:41:26,960 --> 00:41:27,800
Could it be

825
00:41:28,360 --> 00:41:29,480
that she told you

826
00:41:30,180 --> 00:41:31,140
your left hand

827
00:41:31,510 --> 00:41:32,220
is useless?

828
00:41:33,670 --> 00:41:34,670
That you can't use

829
00:41:35,150 --> 00:41:36,480
your left hand anymore?

830
00:41:38,400 --> 00:41:39,230
No.

831
00:41:40,510 --> 00:41:41,390
Oh, I get it.

832
00:41:42,360 --> 00:41:43,400
What she have said

833
00:41:43,960 --> 00:41:46,420
has nothing to do
with your left hand, right?

834
00:41:46,630 --> 00:41:47,630
It must be

835
00:41:48,620 --> 00:41:49,910
something worse.

836
00:41:55,660 --> 00:41:56,210
Lai Zhengtian!

837
00:41:56,210 --> 00:41:57,690
I'm going to kill you!

838
00:41:58,110 --> 00:41:58,960
I'm going to kill you!

839
00:41:58,960 --> 00:41:59,760
Calm down!

840
00:41:59,760 --> 00:42:00,680
Don't just stand there!

841
00:42:00,680 --> 00:42:01,410
Help her out!

842
00:42:01,740 --> 00:42:02,990
I'm going to kill you!

843
00:42:03,070 --> 00:42:04,230
I'm going to kill her!

844
00:42:04,230 --> 00:42:04,880
I'm going to kill her!

845
00:42:04,880 --> 00:42:05,670
You're just talking big.

846
00:42:05,670 --> 00:42:06,710
What can you possibly do to me?

847
00:42:06,710 --> 00:42:07,710
I can kill you.

848
00:42:07,710 --> 00:42:08,570
What would you use to kill me?

849
00:42:08,570 --> 00:42:09,710
I'll shoot you with a gun!

850
00:42:09,710 --> 00:42:10,510
Where did you get the gun?

851
00:42:10,510 --> 00:42:11,190
I—

852
00:42:18,880 --> 00:42:20,670
I was just joking.

853
00:42:21,710 --> 00:42:23,320
You all saw it.

854
00:42:24,320 --> 00:42:26,150
I'm just a cripple.

855
00:42:27,070 --> 00:42:28,960
I can't kill anyone.

856
00:42:41,360 --> 00:42:41,960
Chief Tan,

857
00:42:42,550 --> 00:42:44,350
I'll go organize the materials.

858
00:42:49,630 --> 00:42:50,550
I can see that.

859
00:42:52,280 --> 00:42:54,010
I know what you're trying to do.

860
00:42:54,630 --> 00:42:55,190
Really,

861
00:42:55,500 --> 00:42:56,410
we were so close.

862
00:42:56,410 --> 00:42:57,470
Just a little more,

863
00:42:58,280 --> 00:43:00,110
and his mental defenses
would have been broken.

864
00:43:00,110 --> 00:43:01,230
Think about it.

865
00:43:02,150 --> 00:43:03,480
Someone who can get a gun

866
00:43:04,030 --> 00:43:05,320
couldn't be a nobody, could they?
